         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, 26th September 1892 ¶  ¶ I have the honor to submit herewith for your favorable consideration an application for a special advance of £30.- .- ¶  ¶ — ¶  ¶ Thirty pounds —, to enable me to p...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.09.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Allan McLean</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">T92/8908, unit 710, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written by Georg Luehmann and signed by M.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne, 26th September 1892</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to submit herewith for your favorable consideration an application for a special advance of £30.- .-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>—<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Thirty pounds —, to enable me to pay the salaries of J. Minchin and C. French jr.,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles H. French.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>herbarium assistants, for the month of October. Pay for these two officers has been provided on the estimates of my Branch only to the end of September, and I have therefore the honor to solicit that you will be pleased to make provision for them on the Additional Estimates pending their transfer to another Branch of the Public Service.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A draft letter in an unknown hand, dated 4 October, has been crossed out and annotated 'Letter instead' by the Under Secretary, T. Wilson. The draft, headed 'Forwarded to the Under Treasurer', reads: 'I shall be glad if he will be good enough to move the Honorable the Treasurer to authorise the amount applied for in this Advance to be charged temporarily to funds at his disposal, pending provision to meet this expenditure being made on the Additional Estimates of this Department for the current financial ye</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ar. J. Minchin and C. French Jr.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are officers whose services are no longer required at the Government Botanists branch, and provision for their salary was accordingly made for three months only from 1st July last. Up to the present time suitable vacancies have not been found to which they could be transferred.'</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the Additional estimates of expenditure, presented to Parliament on 14 February 1893, the provision for the two herbarium assistants was increased by £270, sufficient to cover the expenditure for the full financial year ending 30 June 1893 (Victoria<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Parliamentary Paper</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B 40, p. 9).</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>This amount was requested in M to A. McLean, 7 December 1892 (in this edition as 92-12-07a).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Govt. Botanist</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Honorable the Chief Secretary</p>
         </div>
